zPdxqcW7TQYoonyJs7424LxrgDnW4K1bYHHaqsLkxDO-yocaQIiCdDGHFn6GKKL5ksKlKCn-5tReINFeTClZ\",\"summary\":[]}"}, {"type": "text", "text": "Fixed the JVM-test side effect.\n\nThe failure happened because `Main.main(...)` with `rhino.use_java_policy_security=true` installed `JavaPolicySecurity` as the JVM-wide Rhino `SecurityController`. That global controller cannot be reset, and later `NativeJavaObjectTest.serializesJavaAdapterWrapper()` attempted to serialize state containing it; `JavaPolicySecurity` is not serializable.\n\nUpdated:\n- `tests/src/net.sourceforge.htmlunit/htmlunit-core-js/2.70.0/src/test/java/net_sourceforge_htmlunit/htmlunit_core_js/MainTest.java`\n\nChange:\n- Before exercising `Main`’s Java policy security path, the test now installs a minimal serializable `SecurityController`.\n- `Main.main(...)` still reaches the `Class#newInstance()` call for `JavaPolicySecurity`, preserving dynamic-access coverage.\n- The attempted global overwrite is caught by `Main.main(...)`, and subsequent tests no longer inherit the non-serializable `JavaPolicySecurity` controller.\n\nI did not run the Gradle test command.", "textSignature": "{\"v\":1,\"id\":\"msg_066d37b73711efa60169f4f6072b1c819e90c477f1d63c8a02\",\"phase\":\"final_answer\"}"}], "api": "openai-responses", "provider": "OCA", "model": "gpt-5.5", "usage": {"input": 788, "output": 887, "cacheRead": 49152, "cacheWrite": 0, "totalTokens": 50827, "cost": {"input": 0, "output": 0, "cacheRead": 0, "cacheWrite": 0, "total": 0}}, "stopReason": "stop", "timestamp": 1777661436012, "responseId": "resp_066d37b73711efa60169f4f5fca038819e8ca2b4cd55a90280"}}
